QuikSkript can be more difficult to read, especially when other people
write it and have their unique connections to the letters. Shavian
Script is best printed as it is quite clear. Moreover, the letters cover
all the sounds of the English alphabet whereas in QuikSkript there is
some fudging. You cannot write as fast in Shavian Script however. I know
both scripts but still enjoy reading Shavian Script. It is a matter of
taste after all.
Sid 



